OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F363A1775131865
OL,3,CFuneral director admits preventing
OL,4,Cburial charges
OL,6,FHe also pleaded guilty to four "foetus
OL,7,Fallegations" of fraud, where he
OL,8,Fpresented ashes to women falsely
OL,9,Fsaying that they were "the remains of
OL,10,Ftheir unborn".
OL,12,FHe admitted a further charge of fraud
OL,13,Fcovering the ashes of 57 people
OL,14,Fbetween 2017 and 2024, and one of
OL,15,Ffraudulent trading relating to funeral
OL,16,Fplans between 2012 and 2024.
